Not only is traveling by train a great way to see more of your destination, it also scores points for sustainability. And Europe has some of the most scenic train routes in the world. Discover five of the best train trips for exploring the continent from tracks that wind around the snow-capped Alps to journeys through the Norwegian mountains along vast, blue fjords

Discover the untamed grandeur of Norways nature on the trip from Oslo to Bergen High up on Norways Hardangervidda plateau rests one of the worlds most impressive railways Oslo to Bergen. It travels from the Norwegian capital through a wilderness of mountains, tumbling waterfalls, and navy blue fjords so still they appear like mirrors. Enjoy a cultural evening in Oslos grandiose waterfront glass and marble Opera House. Or disembark for a few days of wild swimming in clear mountain springs and hiking through green forest-cloaked valleys. Theres also the option to stop and cross-country ski on the way, plus the chance to visit a fish market founded in the 13th century. Book yourself a stylish suite at Clarion Hotel The Hub while in Oslo.
